<TEXT>
<P>
I want to thank the creators and writers of "The Wonder Years" for producing 
the most brilliant comedy series since "Taxi." I am 33 years old and grew up in 
western Pennsylvania, where I was Kevin Arnold's age in the '60s. It seems as 
though that series was made about my life. We said and did everything they do 
in the show. "Wonder Years" is a comedy filled with sad moments, dramatic 
moments and hilarious moments -- not just a stream of silly punch lines. Thanks 
for the careful thought, research and quality that goes into such a wonderful 
series. 
</P>
<P>
James J. Germann, Northridge 
</P>
</TEXT>
