<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUPPORTS TEST FOR SENIOR DISCOUNTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In reference to the Torrance user fee services article (Times, Feb. 10.), I am 
a strong believer in the 100% individual fee-for-service concept. Some examples 
are the utilization of national parks, private aviation and boating, etc. Also 
a surcharge should be assessed for excessive library use. In regard to senior 
discounts, I heartily approve of those by private enterprises, such as coffee 
shops, restaurants, beauty and barber shops, etc. However, for public 
facilities, such as adult education, there should be a means test similar to 
those for school lunches. I question the 50% discount for affluent seniors over 
the age of 62 1/2 years old, provided by the Torrance Unified School District 
for Adult Education. Similarly, after observing many expensive autos parked at 
surplus cheese distribution locations, a means test should be applied. I 
(would) rather see this surplus cheese given to the poor and homeless. 
</P>
<P>
JIM NISHIZAKA 
</P>
<P>
Torrance 
</P>
</TEXT>
