<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIROHITO'S FUNERAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I cannot find the words to describe the feelings I am undergoing regarding 
President Bush's trip to Japan for the funeral of Hirohito. 
</P>
<P>
I remember so well the three years-plus I spent as a young Marine in the 
Pacific. I cannot forget all the dead on all those islands. The remains of all 
the sailors and Marines entombed on the Arizona, the death marches -- dear God, 
has it all been forgotten? 
</P>
<P>
Bush did not have to go. I feel such sorrow and such shame for us all. 
</P>
<P>
M. RAY FENSTER 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
