<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOCIAL WORKER'S TRAGIC DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The tragedy of Robbyn Panitch's death is overwhelming to her parents as well as 
all of us. Hopefully, her tragedy will not prevent others from pursuing the 
noblest goals of helping people in distress. 
</P>
<P>
It is disturbing, however, to note the reactions of her parents in distress. 
Her father, "a Democratic Party activist," was liberal in his blame of Prop. 
13, Gov. George Deukmejian and former President Ronald Reagan. Never mind that 
a guard at the entrance of the facility would most likely have had little 
effect, that the ACLU has to a large degree been responsible for keeping 
violent, psychiatric people in the streets if they do not agree to be 
hospitalized, that Ms. Panitch voluntarily and altruistically entered a 
profession with a high degree of potential violence (even responding to 911 
emergency calls to strange behavior), that her parents' politics probably were 
a factor in steering her to devotion to the public good with an increased 
exposure to potential violence. 
</P>
<P>
Mr. Panitch, there are many problems in our society which need correction and 
improvement. All of us, liberal as well as conservative, deplore tragedies such 
as occurred to your daughter. We obviously have different ideas and concepts on 
how to approach many of society's problems. However, your liberal heart ought 
to include the ability to intellectualize that good is not captive of liberals, 
while evil is not pervasive in conservatives. Honest men honestly differ. 
</P>
<P>
SAUL H. SANDERS 
</P>
<P>
Palos Verdes Estates 
</P>
