<HEADLINE>
<P>
HITTING NAIL ON THE BISHOP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For those of us who have grown weary of reading totally irrelevant accounts of 
what prominent women in the news are wearing, it was indeed inspiring to learn 
from Betty Cuniberti ("The Bishop of Controversy," Feb. 15) that Barbara 
Harris, the first female bishop of the Episcopal Church, has "manicured mauve 
nails." 
</P>
<P>
Next will we know whether Bishop Tutu bites his and the Pope prefers clippers 
to scissors? What is the View section calling this series: Manicures and 
Morals? Christianity and the Cuticle? 
</P>
<P>
CAROLYN A. WIDENER 
