<HEADLINE>
<P>
AIDS OUTREACH TEAM ADDED TO DRUG ABUSE CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTA FE SPRINGS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An AIDS outreach team has been added to the counseling services offered by Los 
Angeles Centers for Alcohol and Drug Abuse in this community. 
</P>
<P>
The team's goal is to provide AIDS education and prevention services to the 
center's clients. The AIDS service complements existing services at the center 
such as outpatient counseling, drug-diversion sessions, drunk-driving classes 
and youth services. 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles Centers for Alcohol and Drug Abuse is a cooperative effort between 
the Rio Hondo Community Action Network and Open Door Clinics, two nonprofit 
agencies that have provided treatment for substance abuse to many communities 
for 18 years. 
</P>
<P>
The Rio Hondo Community Action Network is at 11769 Telegraph Road. Programs and 
service information can be obtained by calling 949-2381. 
</P>
</TEXT>
