<HEADLINE>
<P>
FLIPPING OUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regularly each week, I read the entire Book Review section to an elderly friend 
who is blind. She can be a little testy. Three-fourths of the way through 
Richard Eder's "Richard Poor" Endpapers, she interrupted with, "Yes, yes. Let's 
stop before he says that reverses are proverbial." 
</P>
<P>
I obeyed willingly. It is a poor piece, clumsily arch. 
</P>
<P>
FRED SCIFERS 
</P>
<P>
INGLEWOOD 
</P>
