The Bush Administration is reviewing visa requests by two officials of the 
Palestine Liberation Organization and a West Bank Palestinian to attend a 
U.S.-Israeli-Palestinian conference in New York next weekend, the State 
Department said. A visa request for a fourth person, Bassam abu Sharif, a PLO 
