<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRAVEL NEWS AND BRIEFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By NORMAN DASH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A slide show of biking and walking tours in Europe will be presented by 
Progressive Travels, a Seattle-based specialist in adventure-travel 
itineraries, at 7:30 p.m. Wednesday in the Plaza Room, Hyatt Wilshire, 3515 
Wilshire Blvd., Los Angeles. Admission free. For more information, call (800) 
245-2229. 
</P>
<P>
 -- -- -- 
</P>
<P>
A slide show on "Sharing the Canadian Wilderness" will be presented by REI, an 
outdoor gear and clothing store, at 6:30 p.m. Thursday at the store, 3029 E. 
University Ave., San Diego. Admission free. For more information, call (619) 
295-7700. 
</P>
<P>
 -- -- -- 
</P>
<P>
The British Columbia Trade and Tourism Office has officially opened at 2600 
Michelson Drive, Suite 1050, Irvine 92715. For travel information, call (800) 
663-6000 or (714) 852-1054. 
</P>
<P>
 -- -- -- 
</P>
<P>
For the latest information on skiing in Austria, call (213) 479-0940. This 
report is updated twice a week, Mondays and Wednesdays. Also, skiing 
information is available at the Austrian National Tourist Office, 11601 
Wilshire Blvd., Suite 2480, Los Angeles, or call (213) 477-3332. NORMAN DASH 
</P>
</TEXT>
