<P>
SANTA CLARA ROLLS TO 78-54 VICTORY IN 2-A SHOWDOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM HAMILTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Santa Clara High School rode a 16-2 scoring spree in the second quarter to a 
78-54 victory over Orange Lutheran Saturday in the Southern Section 2-A 
division boys' championship game in the Sports Arena. 
</P>
<P>
The Saints (23-3) shot 57% from the field and limited Orange Lutheran to its 
lowest scoring output of the season with pressure man-to-man defense. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Clara made 19 of 30 attempts in the first half and led, 45-22, at 
halftime. Center Bubba Burrage made three straight shots as the Saints opened a 
35-17 lead midway through the second quarter, and Orange Lutheran never 
recovered. 
</P>
<P>
Orange Lutheran (23-4) had averaged 84.6 points per game, but forward Daryl 
Cole was the only starter who played well. Cole scored 22 points, but center 
Pat Bagatourian was held to 13 points. 
</P>
<P>
The Lancers shot only 32% after averaging 55% all season. Bagatourian, a 62% 
shooter, made only two of 10 shots. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Clara's 6-foot-5 junior forward Shon Tarver led all scorers with 23 
points, making 10 of 17 shots. He also blocked three shots. TOM HAMILTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
