<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY LINES: DOWN-SIZING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Sam Hall Kaplan 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With the major film studios breaking up into small production companies, many 
of the new shops are looking for offices away from the studio lots and 
corporate office towers. The result has been a run on attractive, easily 
accessible low-rise office buildings on the far Westside and in Santa Monica. 
</P>
<P>
A development consortium, including a few film producers, are recycling the 
architecturally anonymous Systems Development building at 3000 W. Olympic 
Blvd., Santa Monica, into a distinctive garden office complex, to be called the 
Lantana Center. 
</P>
<P>
This interesting experiment in architectural retrofitting and commercial 
development is being done by architect Arthur Pereira and the landscape 
architecture firm of Carter, Romanek.Sam Hall Kaplan 
</P>
