<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHAIN SAW USE REQUIRES WATCH FOR INTERNAL STRESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
If you cut wood with a chain saw, be sure to position yourself so as to prevent 
the cut log section from rolling. Solo Inc. advises holding the saw on the 
right side of your body, outside the line of sight across the chain. If the log 
shows signs of internal stress -- a bowed appearance -- the operator should not 
cut on the stressed side, since this could lead to pinching and result in a 
kickback of the saw. 
</P>
</TEXT>
