<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOME BUYERS' CHOICE OF MORTGAGES GAUGED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From the Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Home buyers, apparently choosing higher monthly payments and lower interest 
paid over a longer term, prefer a 15-year fixed-rate mortgage as their first 
mortgage option, according to a recent study. 
</P>
<P>
The consumer study, by Better Homes and Gardens Real Estate Service, showed 
that 40.3 percent of respondents preferred the 15-year fixed rate mortgage, 
compared with 39.3 percent who would choose a 30-year fixed-rate loan. Eleven 
percent would prefer adjustable rate loans and 5 percent would opt for a 
30-year fixed-rate bimonthly mortgage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
