<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREFERENCE FOR THREE-BEDROOM HOMES REPORTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The dream house of a nationally representative sample of families polled by 
Professional Builder magazine is a three-bedroom, two-bath ranch-style house 
with 1,900 square feet and an average price of $121,000. 
</P>
<P>
They want brick siding (45%) -- except in the West where stucco is the 
preferred exterior material and the East where wood siding is the preferred 
material; a two-car garage (63.5%), traditional architecture (35.5%), a full 
basement (77.8%) and a master bedroom suite with walk-in closet and a private 
bath. The overwhelming number of shoppers (84.6%) want a detached house on its 
own lot. 
</P>
<P>
The survey in the magazine's December issue is based on 1,072 replies from 
families who said they would purchase a home within six months. Along with a 
separate survey questioning builders about their construction and marketing 
practices, it was conducted by National Family Opinion Inc. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Poll or Survey 
</P>
