<P>
REVENUES SOARS AS A-M HOMES MARKS FIRM'S 10TH ANNIVERSARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This year marks the 10th anniversary of A-M Homes, a Santa Barbara-based home 
builder that has grown from annual revenues of $1 million in 1979 to an 
estimated $171 million in revenues for 1988. 
</P>
<P>
With 24 developments under way in both Northern and Southern California and in 
Arizona, A-M Homes -- the name comes from the last names of founders James B. 
(Bart) Araujo and Michael Muench -- is a major player in one of the most 
competitive housing markets in the nation. 
</P>
<P>
It's also a company with plenty of capitalization, especially since last 
October, when Jennings Industries Ltd. of Australia provided additional capital 
of more than $25 million to A-M. 
</P>
<P>
Muench said the infusion of capital will strengthen A-M's position in home 
building, especially in California. 
</P>
<P>
A-M Homes ranked 80th nationally on the "Builder 100" published last year by 
Builder magazine, a trade publication. The firm's total 1987 sales volume was 
$144.7 million. 
</P>
