<P>
'INDOOR AIR POLLUTION' TO BE DISCUSSED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The sixth annual Lungs and the Environment Conference, "Indoor Air Pollution," 
will be held April 1 from 8 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.. under the sponsorship of the 
American Lung Assn. of Los Angeles County. 
</P>
<P>
The one-day, continuing education conference at the University Hilton, 3540 S. 
Figueroa St., is aimed at medical professionals, real estate agents, architects 
and health and safety professionals. Conference topics include: Where to go for 
help, symptoms, chemicals as indoor air pollutants, radon, pesticides and 
fungal contaminants and polices and legislation. 
</P>
<P>
The fee is $45 advance or $50 at the door (students, $25 and $30). Information: 
Marianna Buntich 213/935-5864 or 818/797-5864, Ext. 237. 
</P>
</TEXT>
