<TEXT>
<P>
On paper, Chaminade High figured to play Alemany close Saturday in the second 
round of the Westside baseball tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Four Eagles starters returned from last year's Southern Section 2-A Division 
playoff team, and, although Alemany plays in a larger division, the team is 
coming off a sub-par season. And that was with ace left-hander Joey Rosselli, 
who is out for at least a month because of a broken hand. 
</P>
<P>
Shows how much weight paper carries. 
</P>
<P>
Alemany broke open a 2-1 game with a seven-run fourth inning and went on to a 
22-3 win over visiting Chaminade. 
