<HEADLINE>
<P>
OUTTAKES: BATWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAT H. BROESKE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
They remake movies all the time. But . . . bubblegum cards? 
</P>
<P>
According to a company rep, Topps Co. Inc. will soon produce a deluxe edition 
of 143 Batman cards first released in 1966, featuring paintings of the Caped 
Crusader and his friends/foes. 
</P>
<P>
Price: $20 at comic book ships, no gum included. 
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, "Blind Justice" -- the three-book Batman series from DC's Detective 
Comics -- is now making its way into comics ships. The Books -- Nos. 598, 599 
and the 50th anniversary issue, 600 -- are co-written by Sam Hamm, a new-comer 
to the ranks of comic book writers. 
</P>
<P>
Hamm wrote the story and co-scripted Warners' much talked-about, upcoming (June 
23) feature, "Batman." PAT H. BROESKE 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
