<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOFTBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
VILLA PARK, WESTERN WIN IN SEMIFINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Monique Hernandez pitched a four-hitter to lead Villa Park High School to a 6-1 
victory over Fullerton in a semifinal game of the Fullerton softball tournament 
Saturday at Lion's Field in Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
Michele D'Amato had three hits, including a bases-loaded triple and a double, 
and four RBIs for Villa Park, which plays Western Monday for the championship. 
</P>
<P>
In other Fullerton tournament games: 
</P>
<P>
Western 2, Esperanza 0 -- Western advanced in the winners' bracket behind Beth 
Queypo's shutout. 
</P>
<P>
Magnolia 4, Santiago 0 -- Magnolia's Amber Elliot pitched a no-hitter with 
eight strikeouts to beat Santiago in the losers' bracket. 
</P>
<P>
In nonleague softball: 
</P>
<P>
Garden Grove 1-5, Ocean View 0-3 -- Stephanie Smith pitched a four-hit shutout 
in the first game for host Garden Grove. In the second game, Brandie Novak 
doubled in two runs to break a 3-3 tie in the seventh inning. 
</P>
<P>
Canyon 12-8, Los Amigos 1-1 -- The Comanches limited Los Amigos to three hits 
and two unearned runs in the season-opening doubleheader at Canyon. Canyon's 
Sara Roberts gave up a bunt single to the first batter she faced -- Renee 
Hernandez -- and didn't allow another hit the rest of the way. Kristin Heizer 
pitched a two-hitter in the second game. Canyon first baseman Tina French had 
five hits and four RBIs on the day. Krissy Kyriazis had three hits and scored 
four runs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
