Tuesday: 11:53 ER, 8:00 N/CT, 12:14 ICU 
</P>
<P>
Wednesday: 31:36 N/CT, 8:36 ICU 
</P>
<P>
Friday: 15:10 N/CT 
</P>
<P>
Saturday: 2:47 N/CT, 2:47 ICU 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Whittier Hospital Medical Center 
</P>
<P>
Sunday: 17:00 ICU 
</P>
<P>
Monday: 13:35 N/CT 
</P>
<P>
Tuesday: 13:20 N/CT, 9:00 ICU 
</P>
<P>
Wednesday: 7:00 ICU, 7:00 N/CT 
</P>
<P>
Thursday: 4:36 N/CT 
</P>
<P>
Friday: 1:42 N/CT 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
ICU: Intensive Care Unit saturation -- Hospital's ICUs do not have any 
available beds or taff to care for additional patients. 
</P>
<P>
N/CT: Neuro/CT scan saturation -- Hospital is unable to provide appropriate 
care due to non-functioning CT scan or unavailability of a neurosurgeon. 
(Neuro/CT scan saturation figures are not included for St. Luke Medical Center 
because it has no on-call neurosurgeon.) 
</P>
<P>
ER: Emergency Department saturation -- Emergency department resources are fully 
committed and are not available for additional incoming critically or seriously 
ill mobile intensive-care-unit patients. 
</P>
<P>
T: Trauma saturation -- Hospital does not have any available beds or staff to 
care for incoming trauma patients. 
</P>
<P>
SOURCE: Los Angeles County Department of Health Services. 
</P>
